]]'' magazine.<ref>Nalbone, John. [http://www.nj.com/sports/times/index.ssf?/base/sports-7/1294469140311900.xml&coll=5 \"Peddie product Perez in Garza deal\"], ''[[The Times (Trenton)]]'', January 8, 2011. Accessed February 5, 2011.</ref>\n* [[Haley Peters]] (born 1992), professional [[women's basketball]] forward with the [[Atlanta Dream]] of the [[Women's National Basketball Association]].<ref>Franklin, Paul. [https://www.nj.com/times-sports/2013/03/peddie_school_grad_peters_has.html \"Peddie School grad Peters has led Duke women into the Sweet 16\"], ''[[The Times (Trenton)]]'', March 29, 2013. Accessed July 16, 2019. \"While Haley Peters\u2019 basketball skills have improved every year since her days at The Peddie School, what hasn\u2019t changed is her will to win.\"</ref>\n* [[John Plant (coach)|John Plant]] (1877-1954), basket player who served as head coach for the [[Bucknell Bison men's basketball]] team from 1926-1932.\n* [[Myron Rolle]] (born 1986), Rhodes Scholar who played [[Safety (gridiron football position)|safety]] in the NFL for the [[Tennessee Titans]].<ref>Nutt, Amy Ellis. [http://www.nj.com/insidejersey/index.ssf/2009/03/mr_everything.html \"Jersey's Myron Rolle -- Mr. Everything\"], ''[[The Star-Ledger]]'', March 19, 2009. Accessed March 16, 2012. \"In fact, Rolle has to reach back to the third grade when asked about the last time he got in trouble.Instead, fame came calling at an early age, with stellar schoolboy careers at the Peddie School in Hightstown and then the Hun School in Princeton.\"</ref>\n* [[Richard Sachs]] (born 1953; class of 1971), custom bicycle frame maker.<ref>Brady, Patrick. [http://www.pelotonmagazine.com/Artisans/content/17/380/Richard-Sachs-Part-2 \"Richard Sachs Part 2\"], ''Peloton''. Accessed November 12, 2012. \"Patrick Brady: Have you held other positions in the industry? Richard Sachs: No. Actually, I have never done anything else (for pay) since I left The Peddie School in 1971.\"</ref><ref>Wolff-Mann, Ethan. [ht